Select All Columns<pre><code>SELECT *
FROM entity_name;
</code></pre> <p>The <code>*</code> symbol means "all columns".</p>

Select Specific Columns<pre><code>SELECT column1, column2
FROM entity_name;
</code></pre> <p>This query would display only <code>column1</code> and <code>column2</code>.</p>

Add a New Pupil<pre><code>INSERT INTO Pupils (StudentNum, Forename, Surname, Age)
VALUES (13, 'Emma', 'Brown', 15);
</code></pre> <p>This would add a new pupil record to the <code>Pupils</code> table.</p>

Delete a Pupil<pre><code>DELETE FROM Pupils
WHERE StudentNum = 13;
</code></pre> <p>This would remove Emma Brown's record from the table.</p> <p>Warning</p> <p>Always check your <code>WHERE</code> clause carefully. If you omit the <code>WHERE</code> clause, all records in the table may be deleted.</p>
